sted. When you launch the Cloud IDE, you are presented with a 'dedicated co=
mputer on the cloud' exclusively for you. This is available to you as long =

import dash_core_components as dcc
from dash.dependencies import Input, Output

k-DV0101EN-SkillsNetwork/Data%20Files/airline_data.csv</span>',=20
                            encoding =3D <span class=3D"hljs-string">"ISO-8=
859-1"</span>,

rt</span><span class=3D"hljs-symbol">':</span> str, <span class=3D"hljs-sym=

                                   <span class=3D"hljs-symbol">'Div2Airport=
</span><span class=3D"hljs-symbol">':</span> str, <span class=3D"hljs-symbo=
l">'Div2TailNum</span><span class=3D"hljs-symbol">':</span> str})

app =3D dash.Dash(<span class=3D"hljs-name">__name__</span>)
                              =20
app.layout =3D html.Div(<span class=3D"hljs-name">children=3D</span>[ html.=

=3D{<span class=3D"hljs-symbol">'textAlign</span><span class=3D"hljs-symbol=

n>}),

ss=3D"hljs-symbol">'input-year</span>', value=3D<span class=3D"hljs-symbol"=
>'2010</span>',=20
                                type=3D<span class=3D"hljs-symbol">'number<=

">40</span>}),

'line-plot</span>')),

=3D"hljs-symbol">'figure</span>'),

class=3D"hljs-symbol">'input-year</span>', component_property=3D<span class=
=3D"hljs-symbol">'value</span>'))

def get_graph(<span class=3D"hljs-name">entered_year</span>):

n class=3D"hljs-symbol">'Year</span>']=3D=3Dint(<span class=3D"hljs-name">e=
ntered_year</span>)]
   =20
    # Group the data by Month and compute average over arrival delay time.

pan class=3D"hljs-symbol">'ArrDelay</span>'].mean().reset_index()

pan class=3D"hljs-name">x=3Dline_data</span>[<span class=3D"hljs-symbol">'M=
onth</span>'], y=3Dline_data[<span class=3D"hljs-symbol">'ArrDelay</span>']=
, mode=3D<span class=3D"hljs-symbol">'lines</span>', marker=3Ddict(<span cl=

)))

=3D"hljs-symbol">'Month</span> vs Average Flight Delay Time', xaxis_title=
=3D<span class=3D"hljs-symbol">'Month</span>', yaxis_title=3D<span class=3D=
"hljs-symbol">'ArrDelay</span>')
    return fig
